CLEVELAND METROPOLITAN BAR ASSOCIATION
v.
ZOLLER AND MAMONE. No. 2014-1389 Supreme Court of Ohio. Submitted January 25, 2018
Decided January 26, 2018

{¶ 5} For earlier case, see Cleveland Metro. Bar Assn. v. Zoller and Mamone , 149 Ohio St.3d 125, 2016-Ohio-7639, 73 N.E.3d 476.

O'Connor, C.J., and O'Donnell, Kennedy, French, O'Neill, Fischer, and DeWine, JJ., concur.

*1236{¶ 1} This cause came on for further consideration upon the filing of an application for reinstatement by respondent, Nancy Anne Zoller, Attorney Registration No. 0037933, last known business address in Lyndhurst, Ohio.

{¶ 2} The court coming now to consider its order of November 8, 2016, wherein the court, pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(12)(A)(3), suspended respondent from the practice of law for a period of one year, finds that respondent has substantially complied with that order and with the provisions of Gov.Bar R. V(24).

{¶ 3} Therefore, it is ordered by this court that Nancy Anne Zoller is reinstated to the practice of law in the state of Ohio.

{¶ 4} It is further ordered that the clerk of this court issue certified copies of this order as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(17)(D)(1) and that publication be made as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(17)(D)(2).
